The paper deals with computational geometry and polytopes, which are typical topics in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses combinatorial optimization and integer programming, which are related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper mentions secondary, resultant, and discriminant polytopes, which are topics in cs.SC (Symbolic Computation).
